The '''Bank of America Building''', also called '''Oakland Bank Building''' and '''Oakland Bank of Savings''', is a {{convert|69|m|abbr=on}} [[high-rise]] located in downtown [[Oakland, California]].  The building was originally constructed with nine floors, and the 18-story tower was  annexed  later. It was built as a headquarters for the Oakland Bank, which was acquired by Bank of America in 1929.

